# YGOPro Backup

Python CLI (3.12+, `uv`) to backup YGOPro card data from YGOPRODeck and convert card images to lossless WEBP.

## Layout

- `main.py` — root entry; delegates to `src/cli.py`
- `src/cli.py` — argparse subcommands
- `src/backup_data.py` — `backup-data` → `backup/data/data.json`
- `src/backup_images.py` — `backup-images <url>` → `backup/images/*.webp`
- `backup/` — output only; not source

Run: `uv run main.py backup-data` or `uv run main.py backup-images <url>`.

New commands: add `src/<module>.py`, wire subcommand in `src/cli.py`.

## Console output

Use [Rich](https://rich.readthedocs.io/) for all CLI console output. Import the shared `console` from `src.console` and prefer markup (`[bold]`, `[green]`, `[yellow]`, etc.), `Table`, and `Panel` where they improve readability.

## Agent

Never run `main.py` unless the user explicitly asks.
